The spark of hopeless hope has not been quite quenched by her long sorrow. Look again how much loving pride is ex- pressed by the two words of Aeneas—⁶ Hectoris Andromache? Further on we notice one of those ‘pathetic half-lines,’ the only one that leaves the sense unfinished. Itis where she should speak of the lost Creusa, but to us the pathos is deepened by the thought that the master's hand was cold ere he could mould to beauty the tender thought that was in his mind when working at this scene.
